node.text: Today, I spoke at the National Association for Drug Court Professionals, a charity that develops strategies within the judicial system that empower people to change their lives.  It wasn’t until I went to jail for some indiscretions that I knew I needed to change my life around.  I thank God every day for the professionals who disciplined me with compassion and fairness.  Thank you @nadcp for recognizing that we all make mistakes and could use a second chance in life.  Love. Light. Leslie.

node.text: I have so much to learn from my adored friend @brandicarlile, and I think that her struggle with a faith that once rejected her would provide comfort to many other souls as well. She learned to see past all the narrow peripherals of that faith to find and embrace its fundamental spirit.  She lives by that spirit today, and her music and her thrilling voice are an invitation to others to share her peace.  Please visit her page and grab your copy of Broken Horses which is out now.  You can also find our whole conversation where this video clip was taken.  Love. Light. Leslie. @thetanyatucker

node.text: “At times of stress, at times of peace, I would recite the old words and hum the sturdy tunes, and the weariness of years, the burdens of time would melt away. I found myself, as I find myself to this day, revived and renewed, if only for the length of a few beloved verses. But how welcome that brief restoration of a child’s fleeting and marvelous belief can be. “. Thank ALL of you for taking this journey with me.  @weareplatoon @travishoward @dannymyrick @dollyparton @eddievedder @chrisstapleton @morganwithane @thetanyatucker @brandicarlile @tjosborne @katiepruittmusic @ashleymcbryde @charlieworsham

node.text: Okay, I’ve been thinking of a fun little concert series to bring y’all.  I think I’ve got it.  Of course, I will have to solicit the help of my sidekick @travishoward.  I will try to bring you the first one this week.

node.text: I love music.  I am not a musician but maybe that is why I gravitate toward good folks who are.  I appreciate the things I am not good at.  Don’t we all? Music and sports seem to bind us all together in one way or another.  So, here is a short list of my current “go to” music (scroll through). Also, feel free to let me know who y’all are listening to as well. @thewarandtreaty @lukasnelsonofficial @brothersosborne @fancyhagood @katiepruittmusic @thetanyatucker @chrisstapleton @brandicarlile @sturgillsimpson

node.text: Hey @lukasnelsonofficial, I love your new album so much that I had to have the physical version.  Would you please autograph my copy? Oh, I couldn’t help to find my own album while I was there.  Y’all need to stream, buy, add A Few Stars Apart to your collection — you’ll thank me later.

node.text: Today, I spoke at the National Association for Drug Court Professionals, a charity that develops strategies within the judicial system that empower people to change their lives.  It wasn’t until I went to jail for some indiscretions that I knew I needed to change my life around.  I thank God every day for the professionals who disciplined me with compassion and fairness.  Thank you @nadcp for recognizing that we all make mistakes and could use a second chance in life.  Love. Light. Leslie.
